rComments: utsc's finest by far. needs to teach more courses.

Professor Fraser was very kind and extremely humble.  He really loves what he's teaching, and will give funny stories about his time at Oxford and Cambridge. The course is hard, but if you show that you tried to understand it, you will do well.  Go to his office hours for help.  It got me an 87

Prof. Fraser is one of those profs that will never leave your mind even 100 yrs from now - if you live that long. He's very well educated as the post bellow says and most importantly he's very humble. Show him you're hardworking and you'll get the mark you want. Hard to follow him in class but he always makes himself available for help.Much respect

THIS TEACHER IS BY FAR THE GREATEST TEACHER KNOWN TO MAN...He's so nice and so helpful its not even funny. He's a kind man and very intelligent, I mean that's something you'd expect from someone educated at oxford and cambridge no?. Noone understands nething, yet they still do well...Great Teacher.
